UPON HIS GRADUATION FROM PENN IN 1958, HE WENT ON TO EARN HIS JURIS DOCTORATE DEGREE FROM NEW YORK UNIVERSITY'S SCHOOL OF LAW AND WAS A CAPTAIN IN THE UNITED STATES COAST GUARD. MR. JOHNSON PRACTICED LAW IN NEW YORK CITY BEFORE FINDING HIS TRUE CALLING ON WALL STREET. MR. JOHNSON'S CAREER BEGAN AT KUHN LOEB WHICH LATER MERGED WITH LEHMAN BROTHERS IN 1977. HE WAS A PARTNER AT LEHMAN BROTHERS WHICH WAS THE PINNACLE OF HIS WORK LIFE. HE ABSOLUTELY LOVED THE CAMARADERIE OF HIS LEHMAN PARTNERS AND ASSOCIATES AND RETIRED SHORTLY AFTER THE "GREAT HOUSE OF LEHMAN" MERGED WITH SHEARSON

Paid Notice: Memorials  MAZZEO, ALBERTO DANIEL DIED PEACEFULLY AT CALVARY HOSPITAL IN THE BRONX ON JANUARY 29, 2016 AFTER A YEAR, LONG ILLNESS. HE HAD THE CONSTANT AND LOVING SUPPORT OF HIS SPOUSE MITCH MONDELLO, NEIGHBORS, FRIENDS, UN COLLEAGUES AND FAMILY IN ARGENTINA AND ITALY. ALBERTO'S GENEROSITY OF SPIRIT, COURAGE AND OPTIMISM WAS EXEMPLIFIED BY HIS ANSWER WHENEVER ANYONE ASKED HIM HOW HE WAS: "I'M OK, I'M GETTING BETTER." AND OF COURSE BY HIS EXUBERANT LAUGHTER AND LOVE OF MALBEC. IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALBERTO'S WISHES, HIS ASHES WILL BE SCATTERED IN THE HUDSON RIVER AND THE RIO DE LA PLATA, THE RIVERS FLOWING THROUGH THE TWO CITIES THAT HE CONSIDERED HOME. A MEMORIAL MASS AND INTERMENT WILL TAKE PLACE IN ZACCANOPOLI, HIS ANCESTRAL HOME IN CALABRIA. 1
